<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1436,1907,2042]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3027114301" country="Iran" county="Chorion" location="Dezful" municipality="Robust" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" specimenCount="10">
Egg (similar to that in 
<figureCitation box="[414,481,1907,1934]" captionStart="FIGURES 5–7" captionStartId="31.[151,264,446,470]" captionTargetBox="[413,1176,187,416]" captionTargetId="figure-19@31.[408,1179,181,422]" captionTargetPageId="31" captionText="FIGURES 5–7. Eggs, lateral outline: 5, Colobaea pectoralis (Zetterstedt); 6, C. americana Steyskal; 7, C. bifasciella (Fallén). Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405550" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405550/files/figure.png" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
) (based on 
<specimenCount box="[618,772,1907,1934]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="generic">10 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A25FFF0FC94F8DB8DBEDB95" box="[844,923,1907,1933]" country="Iran" county="Chorion" municipality="Robust" name="Dezful" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Dezful</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[936,986,1908,1934]" name="Iran" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Iran</collectingCountry>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A25FFF0FC37F8DB8A1BDB95" box="[1007,1086,1907,1933]" country="Iran" county="Chorion" municipality="Robust" name="Length" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Length</location>
<quantity box="[1095,1263,1907,1934]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.5" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="0.45" valueMax="0.5" valueMin="0.4">0.40–0.50 mm</quantity>
; greatest width 
<quantity box="[151,317,1944,1970]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" metricValueMax="1.7999999999999998" metricValueMin="1.4" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" unit="mm" value="0.16" valueMax="0.18" valueMin="0.14">0.14–0.18 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[327,409,1943,1969]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Robust</collectingMunicipality>
, spindle shaped; anterior and posterior ends smoothly rounded; ventral surface more convex than dorsal surface in lateral aspect. 
<collectingCounty box="[558,650,1979,2005]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Chorion</collectingCounty>
finely punctate, sculptured into polygonal cells; longitudinal ridges of cells stronger ventrally, imparting noticeable striated appearance; dorsal surface with reticulate appearance
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
