<subSubSection pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3027114304" country="Iran" county="Mouthhooks" location="Dezful" municipality="Indentation" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="10">
First-instar larva (based on 
<specimenCount box="[510,663,151,177]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="generic">10 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFD04FF3F8D0EDCA9" box="[732,811,151,177]" country="Iran" county="Mouthhooks" municipality="Indentation" name="Dezful" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Dezful</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[823,873,151,177]" name="Iran" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Iran</collectingCountry>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFCA4FF3F8DEEDCA9" box="[892,971,151,177]" country="Iran" county="Mouthhooks" municipality="Indentation" name="Length" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Length</location>
<quantity box="[979,1146,150,177]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.6" valueMax="0.7" valueMin="0.5">0.50–0.70 mm</quantity>
; greatest width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.05" metricValueMax="1.4" metricValueMin="0.7" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.105" valueMax="0.14" valueMin="0.07">0.07–0.14 mm</quantity>
. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFF0AFF148F12DCCE" box="[210,311,188,214]" country="Iran" county="Mouthhooks" municipality="Indentation" name="Post-oral" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Post-oral</location>
spinules very long, slender, recurved, lightly pigmented. 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFC11FF148A86DCCE" box="[969,1187,188,214]" country="Iran" county="Mouthhooks" municipality="Indentation" name="Cephalopharyngeal" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Cephalopharyngeal</location>
skeleton light brown, 
<quantity box="[151,318,225,252]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.5" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="9.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.095" valueMax="0.1" valueMin="0.09">0.09–0.10 mm</quantity>
long. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[397,525,225,251]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Indentation</collectingMunicipality>
index 82–88. 
<collectingCounty box="[698,840,225,251]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Mouthhooks</collectingCounty>
long, slender; pharyngeal sclerites strongly sclerotized
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Posterior end with three pairs of large marginal lobes plus lateral protuberances. Large, darkly pigmented spinules below spiracular plates (
<figureCitation box="[489,573,337,363]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–30" captionStartId="37.[151,264,565,589]" captionTargetBox="[418,1176,187,531]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[408,1179,181,541]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 28–30. Posterior spiracular plates: 28, Colobaea americana Steyskal, first-instar larva; 29, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, first-instar larva; 30, C. deemingi, third-instar larva. Abbreviations: FH, float hair; PGO, perispiracular gland opening. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405560/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 29</figureCitation>
). Spiracular tubes 
<quantity box="[779,892,337,364]" metricMagnitude="-5" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.017">0.017 mm</quantity>
long, slender. Float hairs long, slender. Peri-anal pad large, protrudent, subovate, with apices attenuated.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Second-instar larva (based on four specimens from Dezful, 
<collectingCountry box="[876,926,413,439]" name="Iran" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Iran</collectingCountry>
). Length 
<quantity box="[1033,1172,412,439]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.7" metricValueMax="1.8" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.7" valueMax="1.8" valueMin="1.6">1.6–1.8 mm</quantity>
; greatest width 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.5" metricValueMax="3.0" metricValueMin="2.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.25" valueMax="0.3" valueMin="0.2">0.2–0.3 mm</quantity>
. Body form slender, spindle shaped. Post-oral spinules numerous, large, sharp; cephalopharyngeal skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[160,240,487,513]" captionStart="FIGURES 9–12" captionStartId="32.[151,264,936,960]" captionTargetBox="[434,1141,241,897]" captionTargetId="figure-55@32.[433,1143,237,902]" captionText="FIGURES 9–12. Cephalopharyngeal skeletons: 9, Colobaea pectoralis (Zetterstedt), first-instar larva; 10, C. pectoralis, second-instar larva; 11, C. punctata (Lundbeck), second-instar larva; 12, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, second-instar larva.Abbreviations: DB, dorsal bridge; DC, dorsal cornu; HS, hypostomal sclerite; MH, mouthhook; PS, pharyngeal sclerite; VA, ventral arch; VC, ventral cornu. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4478679" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4478679/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
) dark brown; 
<quantity box="[397,497,487,513]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.2">0.20 mm</quantity>
long. Indentation index 76–80. Pharyngeal sclerites short; dorsal and ventral cornua with incomplete windows; mouthhooks long, with small, recurved hook part; ventral arch small, straplike, with 18–20 small, slender teeth. Anterior spiracles small, with 12–15 marginal papillae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" box="[199,1078,599,625]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Spinules present on lateral pads; segmental spinules sparse, lightly pigmented.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Posterior end with three pairs of large marginal lobes plus lateral protuberances. Mammillae present at bases of ventral lobes. Peritremes lightly pigmented, three spiracular slits in central, pigmented area; no hyaline float hairs (
<figureCitation box="[160,243,711,737]" captionStart="FIGURES 13–14" captionStartId="32.[151,264,1982,2006]" captionTargetBox="[419,1167,1459,1948]" captionTargetId="figure-277@32.[408,1179,1452,1958]" captionTargetPageId="32" captionText="FIGURES 13–14. Posterior spiracular plates of second-instar larvae: 13, Colobaea americana Steyskal; 14, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt. Abbreviations: Pt, peritreme; SpS, spiracular slit; StS, stigmatic scar. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405552" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405552/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3027114308" country="Iran" county="Anterior" location="Dezful" municipality="Body" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" specimenCount="10">
Third-instar larva (based on 
<specimenCount box="[517,669,748,774]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" type="generic">10 specimens</specimenCount>
from 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFD39FD448D15DF1E" box="[737,816,748,774]" country="Iran" county="Anterior" municipality="Body" name="Dezful" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Dezful</location>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[827,877,749,775]" name="Iran" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Iran</collectingCountry>
). 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:7170D74F6A25FFFFFF4FF8838D7DDA79:FC0630826A2AFFFFFCA7FD448DEBDF1E" box="[895,974,748,774]" country="Iran" county="Anterior" municipality="Body" name="Length" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Length</location>
<quantity box="[981,1119,748,775]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.85" metricValueMax="3.5" metricValueMin="2.2" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="2.85" valueMax="3.5" valueMin="2.2">2.2–3.5 mm</quantity>
; greatest width 
<quantity box="[1295,1433,748,775]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.5" metricValueMax="9.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.65" valueMax="0.9" valueMin="0.4">0.4–0.9 mm</quantity>
. 
<collectingMunicipality box="[151,212,785,811]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Body</collectingMunicipality>
form spindle shaped, lateral welts not apparent, posterior half of body not expanded, lateral pads visible. 
<collectingCounty pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Anterior</collectingCounty>
spiracles (
<figureCitation box="[332,413,823,849]" captionStart="FIGURES 32–35" captionStartId="39.[151,264,897,921]" captionTargetBox="[411,1175,240,866]" captionTargetId="figure-45@39.[408,1179,237,874]" captionTargetPageId="39" captionText="FIGURES 32–35. Anterior spiracles, third-instar larvae: 32, Colobaea pectoralis (Zetterstedt); 33, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt; 34, C. punctata (Lundbeck); 35, C. bifasciella (Fallén). Abbreviations: PrS, prismatic spot; StS, stigmatic scar. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405564" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405564/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 33</figureCitation>
) with expanded apical part, 12–14 marginal papillae tightly enclosed by integument
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Cephalopharyngeal skeleton (
<figureCitation box="[538,623,860,886]" captionStart="FIGURES 40–43" captionStartId="43.[151,264,1490,1514]" captionTargetBox="[154,1429,188,1459]" captionTargetId="figure-19@43.[151,1436,181,1466]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 40–43. Cephalopharyngeal skeletons of third-instar larvae: 40, C. punctata, lateral view; 41, C. pectoralis, lateral view; 42, C. bifasciella (Fallén), lateral view; 43. C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, lateral view. Abbreviations: AvP, anteroventral process of pharyngeal sclerite, DB, dorsal bridge, DC, dorsal cornu, DW, dorsal window, ES, epistomal sclerite, HS, hypostomal sclerite, LS, ligulate sclerite, MH, mouthhook, PB, parastomal bars, PS, pharyngeal sclerite, VA, ventral arch, VC, ventral cornu, VW, ventral window. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405572" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405572/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 43</figureCitation>
) dark brown, 
<quantity box="[789,892,860,887]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.4" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="0.34">0.34 mm</quantity>
long. Indentation index 80. Mouthhooks large, hook part directed ventrally. Ventral arch slender, with 18–20 teeth. Several rows of dark spinules by oral opening, lateral to mouthhooks. Dorsal cornu with small, complete window; ventral cornu with large, elongate window; apparent margins of cornua entire.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Spinules present on lateral pads; segments III and IV with ventral spinule patch, segment V with two-part patch, segments VI–XII with three-part patches. Segmental spinules small, lightly pigmented.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Posterior end (
<figureCitation box="[363,444,1084,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 15–20" captionStartId="34.[151,264,1601,1625]" captionTargetBox="[419,1172,567,1572]" captionTargetId="figure-184@34.[414,1172,561,1578]" captionTargetPageId="34" captionText="FIGURES 15–20. Posterior ends of third-instar larvae: 15, Colobaea americana Steyskal, caudal view; 16, C. bifasciella (Fallén), caudal view; 17, C. pectoralis (Zetterstedt), caudal view; 18, C. punctata (Lundbeck), caudal view; 19, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, caudal view; 20, C. punctata, lateral view.Abbreviations: DL, dorsal lobe, LP, lateral pad, M, mammillae, PaP, peri-anal pad, SpP, spiracular plate, SpT, spiracular tube, VL, ventral lobe, VlL, ventrolateral lobe. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405554" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405554/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 19</figureCitation>
) with four pairs of lobes; dorsal pair small, ventral and ventrolateral pairs large, conical; lateral protuberances large, less acute than lobes. Mammillae present at bases of ventral lobes. Peritremes, slit margins, and stigmatic scars lightly pigmented (
<figureCitation box="[646,730,1159,1185]" captionStart="FIGURES 28–30" captionStartId="37.[151,264,565,589]" captionTargetBox="[418,1176,187,531]" captionTargetId="figure-19@37.[408,1179,181,541]" captionTargetPageId="37" captionText="FIGURES 28–30. Posterior spiracular plates: 28, Colobaea americana Steyskal, first-instar larva; 29, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, first-instar larva; 30, C. deemingi, third-instar larva. Abbreviations: FH, float hair; PGO, perispiracular gland opening. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405560" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405560/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Fig. 30</figureCitation>
). Peri-anal pad with lateral margins attenuated into points.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">
Puparium (
<figureCitation box="[322,450,1196,1223]" captionStart="FIGURES 44–48" captionStartId="44.[151,264,1650,1674]" captionTargetBox="[154,1435,386,1615]" captionTargetId="figure-113@44.[151,1436,381,1626]" captionTargetPageId="44" captionText="FIGURES 44–48. Puparia, lateral and dorsal views: 44, Colobaea americana Steyskal, lateral view; 45, C. deemingi Knutson &amp; Bratt, lateral view; 46, C. deemingi, dorsal view; 47, C. punctata (Lundbeck), lateral view; 48, C. punctata, dorsal view. Measurement in mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4405574" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4405574/files/figure.png" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Figs 45–46</figureCitation>
) (based on six specimens from Dezful, 
<collectingCountry box="[888,938,1197,1223]" name="Iran" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Iran</collectingCountry>
). Length 4.1–5.0 mm; greatest width 1.0– 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.1" pageId="40" pageNumber="41" unit="mm" value="1.1">1.1 mm</quantity>
. Typically distorted to fit planorbiform snail host shell. Dorsal surface of segments II–IV dark, reddish brown if host shell is planorbiform or else all exposed surfaces darkly pigmented; other integument tan. Integument subshiny, finely punctate. Segmentation, secondary integumentary folds, and spinules obscure. Lateral pads and lateral longitudinal welts visible on segments IX–XI.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">In dorsal aspect, dorsal cephalic cap flattened and expanded to occlude whorl of host shell; widest at posterior margin of segment V and then narrowed abruptly and continued with margins parallel to those of segment XI, which narrows to rounded end of posterior spiracular disc. Crescent shaped in lateral aspect, segments VI–IX depressed by inner whorl of host shell.</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="40.[151,1437,150,1633]" pageId="40" pageNumber="41">Anterior spiracles small, projecting dorsally from anterolateral angles of cephalic cap; papillae very small. Posterior spiracles large, protrudent from dome-shaped disc; marginal lobes small, pointed. Posterior spiracular disc not darkened. Peri-anal pad suboval, concolorous, not invaginated.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
